article.headline: Siena 83, Holy Cross 71
article.story: WORCESTER, Mass. -- Alex Franklin scored 22 points to lead Siena to an 83-71 victory over Holy Cross on Tuesday. Kenny Hasbrouck scored eight points during a decisive 9-0 second-half run for the Saints (8-4), who have won six of their last seven games. R.J. Evans, a freshman, scored 21 points for Holy Cross (4-9). The Crusaders played without three of their starters, and Siena forced 23 turnovers. The Saints led 41-34 at halftime and extended their lead to 53-41 on Hasbrouck's 3-pointer. Holy Cross cut the advantage to 53-45 with 14:30 left, but Hasbrouck scored and then got another 3-pointer. Hasbrouck stole the ball from Evans and scored two free throws. Owen Wignot then added another steal and also scored two foul shots to give the Saints an insurmountable 62-45 lead with 9:41 left.
